WorkItem.Description:
When a DataGrid is bound to a DataTable that contains a DataColumn whose ColumnName has trailing or leading whitespace, the DataGrid displays the column, but does not display data for that column.  This problem arose when retrieving data from Excel using the JET driver, and a column had a space at the end. 
 
            DataTable table = new DataTable();
            DataColumn columnA = table.Columns.Add("A");
            DataColumn columnB = table.Columns.Add("B ");   // note the space
 
            DataRow newRow = table.NewRow();
            newRow[columnA] = "Test A";
            newRow[columnB] = "Test B";
            table.Rows.Add(newRow);
 
            dataGrid.DataContext = table;  // note that the dataGrid ItemsSource is set to {Binding}
